cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the challenges of defending against adversarial attacks on neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on defensive distillation and the tradeoff between blocking targeted attacks and preserving the network's ability to learn suggests that the paper is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of neural networks for image classification also suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a likely category. Other possible categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
